    "recap_headline": "California State University Northridge Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FRESNO, Calif.\n---CSUN Baseball collected 16 hits and six RBI from freshman\nVaughn Coleman\nin an 11-9 victory over Fresno State on Tuesday at Pete Beiden Field at Bob Bennett Stadium. Coleman belted two home runs in a 3-for-3 day at the plate while\nMateo Rickman\nand\nColton Boardman\ntotaled three hits apiece. All nine Matador starters recorded at least one base hit as CSUN snapped a three game skid.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nCSUN wasted little time jumping in front in the top of the first. After three straight hitters reached base with one out,\nColton Boardman\nrifled an RBI single to deep right to put CSUN on the scoreboard. CSUN added another on a sacrifice fly from\nMatthew Cormier\nfor a 2-0 lead.\nThe Matadors left the bases loaded in the first inning but kept the pressure on the Bulldog pitching staff throughout most of the night. In the second, back-to-back doubles from\nWill Linberg\nand\nMatthew Thomas\nproduced another run. CSUN would then go ahead 4-0 in the third inning behind three straight singles, capped by a Cormier RBI hit.\nAfter\nJack Jones\ntossed a pair of shutout frames to begin the game for CSUN, the Bulldogs broke up the shutout with a solo homer from Caden Munster in the third. The Bulldogs eventually loaded the bases with one out, but CSUN escaped further trouble when reliever\nCharles Rogers\nretired two straight batters to end the inning.\nColeman would put the Matadors back into the scoring column on one swing of the bat in the fifth inning. Rickman set the table with an infield hit while Coleman delivered a two-run homer with two outs to extend to a 6-1 lead.\nThe Bulldogs though kept battling back, plating two runs each in the fifth and sixth innings to pull to within 6-5. CSUN would get a key out to end the sixth when\nLogan Miller\nstruck out Brady Hewitt, maintaining the one-run lead.\nIn the seventh, the Matadors created more breathing room by plating two more runs. Boardman made it a 7-5 game with an RBI single and Coleman knocked in another with a sacrifice fly. Coleman though was far from done at the plate. The Matadors threatened in the ninth with two runners on base and two outs for Coleman. The freshman proceeded to hammer a 0-1 pitch over the left field fence for a three-run homer and an 11-5 CSUN lead.\nDown to their last at bat, the Bulldogs put together a late rally in the bottom of the ninth. All with two outs, the Bulldogs collected a two-run single from Sky Collins, an RBI double from\u00a0 Marcus Nolen and an RBI single from Munster to pull to within 11-9. CSUN though finally shut the door when\nJaiden Turner\nretired Ethan Payne on a flyout to end the ballgame.\nNOTES OF THE GAME\nCSUN improves to 11-9 overall while Fresno State slips to 7-12.\nKody King\nwas credited with the win after tossing two shutout innings over the seventh and eighth innings. He also finished with two strikeouts.\nJones started his first career game for CSUN on the mound, pitching 2.1 innings and allowing\u00a0one run.\nColeman's six RBI set a new\u00a0season\u00a0high while he reached base four times on the night.\nBoth\nAndrew Becker\nand Rickman scored three runs each.\nACCORDING TO COACH EDDIE CORNEJO\n\"Our freshmen showed out today offensively, providing the spark and the RBIs. Great outings from\nLogan Miller\nand\nKody King\nto stop their rallies in a high scoring game made all the difference.\"\nUP NEXT\nCSUN resumes Big West play with a road series at Cal State Fullerton this weekend. The opener is set for Friday at 6:30 p.m. on ESPN+.\n#GoMatadors"
  },
